reted as <i>-born</i> and <i>-bourne</i>, leading to confusion with   Melbourne  ."]}]},{"name":"Piers","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Regular medieval vernacular form of   Peter   (from the Old French nominative case, as against the oblique <i>Pier</i>, modern <i>Pierre</i>). In the form <i>Pierce</i> it survived into the 18th century, although in part this may be a transferred use of the surname derived from the medieval given name. <i>Piers</i> was revived in the mid-20th century, perhaps partly under the influence of  William Langland's  great rambling medieval poem Piers Plowman (  1367–86 ), in which the character of Piers symbolizes the virtues of hard work, honesty, and fairness."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":8,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":17,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":62,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Piers Malbank was born in 1320, in Devon, England. He married Alice de Vernon about 1